Bộ từ vựng về con người, gia đình
woman	/ˈwʊm.ən/	n.	an adult female human	phụ nữ	I prefer to see a woman doctor.
baby	/ˈbeɪ.bi/	n.	a very young child or animal	đứa trẻ	She had a baby last year.
girl	/gɜːl/	n.	a female child	con gái (nói chung)	He married the girl next door.
man	/mæn/	n.	an adult male human	đàn ông	a good-looking young man
parents	/ˈpeə.rənts/	n.	a person's father or mother	bố mẹ	He's still living with his parents.
grandparents	/ˈgrænd.peə.rənts/	n.	the father or mother of your father or mother	ông bà	The children are staying with their grandparents.
husband	/ˈhʌz.bənd/	n.	the man that a woman is married to; a married man	chồng	This is my husband, Steve.
children	/ˈtʃɪl.drən/	n.	a young human who is not yet an adult	trẻ con	They have three grown-up children.
granddaughter	/ˈgrænd.dɔː.təʳ/	n.	a daughter of your son or daughter	cháu gái	
wife	/waɪf/	n.	the woman that a man is married to; a married woman	vợ	She's his second wife.
boy	/bɔɪ/	n.	a male child or a young male person	con trai (nói chung)	Now that she's a teenager, she's starting to be interested in boys.
grandson	/ˈgrænd.sʌn/	n.	a son of your son or daughter	cháu trai	
grandfather	/ˈgrændˌfɑːðəʳ /	n.	the father of your father or mother	ông	
nephew	/ˈnef.juː/	n.	the son of your brother or sister; the son of your husband's or wife's brother or sister	cháu trai (con anh chị em)	
mother	/ˈmʌð.əʳ/	n.	a female parent of a child or animal; a person who is acting as a mother to a child	mẹ	I want to buy a present for my mother and father.
grandmother	/ˈgrænd.mʌð.əʳ/	n.	the mother of your father or mother	bà	
niece	/niːs/	n.	the daughter of your brother or sister; the daughter of your husband's or wife's brother or sister	cháu gái (con anh chị em)	
uncle	/ˈʌŋ.kļ/	n.	the brother of your mother or father; the husband of your aunt	chú, bác trai, cậu	I'm going to visit my uncle.
sister-in-law	/ˈsɪs.tə.rɪn.lɔː/	n.	the sister of your husband or wife; your brother's wife; the wife of your husband or wife's brother	chị/em dâu, chị/em vợ	
cousin	/ˈkʌz.ən/	n.	a child of your aunt or uncle	anh, em họ (con cô, chú, bác)	He's a distant cousin of mine.
father	/ˈfɑː.ðəʳ/	n.	a male parent of a child or an animal; a person who is acting as the father to a child	bố	Ben is a wonderful father.
son	/sʌn/	n.	a person's male child	con trai	We have two sons and a daughter.
daughter	/ˈdɔː.təʳ/	n.	a person's female child	con gái	We have two sons and a daughter.
brother-in-law	/ˈbrʌð.ə.rɪn.lɔː/	n.	the brother of your husband or wife; your sister's husband; the husband of your husband or wife's sister	anh/em rể, anh/em vợ	
brother	/ˈbrʌð.əʳ/	n.	a boy or man who has the same mother and father as another person	anh/em trai	He's my brother.
sister	/ˈsɪs.təʳ/	n.	a girl or woman who has the same mother and father as another person	chị/em gái	She's my sister.
aunt	/ɑːnt/	n.	the sister of your father or mother; the wife of your uncle	bác gái, cô, dì, thím	My aunt lives in Canada.